      "description": "Available is a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), a driver-focused example featuring the M96 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine coupled to a precise 6-speed manual transaxle. This unit features a documented IMS bearing upgrade and a recently inspected rear main seal. Performance is sharp thanks to VarioCam Plus timing and a factory-spec suspension utilizing McPherson struts and a multi-link rear setup for optimal kinematics. The braking system remains high-performance with four-piston monoblock calipers and ventilated, cross-drilled rotors. While the exterior displays minor road-derived patina, the mechanical synchronization, throttle response, and chassis rigidity are excellent, making this a superb candidate for a spirited daily driver or weekend tourer.",
